29/*! \brief Planning stage prior to rewriting in TransformLayoutRewriter
30 *
31 * There are four ways that transformation may be handled. Each
32 * updates the buffer shape and the indices used to acces the buffer
33 * in BufferStore/BufferLoad nodes, but differ in how they handle the
34 * `pad_value`. In order of preference, the different strategies are
35 * as follows:
36 *
37 * 1. NoPaddingRequired. The transformation does not introduce
38 * padding, so only local changes to update the indices of
39 * BufferLoad/BufferStore nodes are required. No blocks are added,
40 * removed, or replaced.
41 *
42 * 2. ProloguePlan. The transformation introduces padding, but the
43 * analyzed block has no write stages for the transformed buffer.
44 * This buffer is an input and the caller is responsible for ensuring
45 * that the padding contains the specified `pad_value`. The generated
46 * prologue contains `builtin::assume()` calls that will expose this
47 * known value during scheduling/simplification, but will be removed
48 * during lowering.
49 *
50 * 3. ReplacementPlan. The transformation introduces padding, has at
51 * least one write stage for the transformed buffer, and at least one
52 * of those write stages writes to all pre-transformation indices
53 * following a row-major traversal. These write stage is rewritten to
54 * be row-major traversals of the post-transformation indices, with a
55 * `tir::if_then_else` call to write either the specified `pad_value`
56 * into padding or the computed value into non-padding.
57 *
58 * 4. EpiloguePlan. The transformation introduces padding, has at
59 * least one write stage for the transformed buffer, but no write
60 * stage can be rewritten to use `tir::if_then_else`. The
61 * transformation still requires the `pad_value` to be written into
62 * the padding, so a new block is inserted after the last write stage
63 * to explicitly fill the padding.
64 *
65 */
66class TransformLayoutPlanner : private StmtExprVisitor {
67 public:
68 // Statement to be inserted prior to the analyzed block
69 struct ProloguePlan {
70 Stmt prologue;
71 };
72
73 // Loops within the analyzed block that should be replaced
74 struct ReplacementPlan {
75 Map<For, Stmt> replacements;
76 Map<Block, Block> new_block_to_old;
77 };
78
79 // The block to be inserted, along with the location at which it
80 // should be inserted. The location will be either a For or a
81 // Block, and will be after all writes the transformed buffer.
82 struct EpiloguePlan {
83 Stmt insert_after;
84 Stmt new_block;
85 };
86
87 struct NoPaddingRequired {};
88
89 using TransformPlan =
90 std::variant<ProloguePlan, ReplacementPlan, EpiloguePlan, NoPaddingRequired>;
91
92 static TransformPlan Plan(Block block, Buffer old_buffer, Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map,
93 IndexMap inverse, PrimExpr padding_predicate,
94 Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) {
95 ICHECK(!pad_value.defined() || pad_value.value()->final_indices.size() == 1)
96 << "Internal error: Should be caught by ScheduleError checks prior to this point";
97 TransformLayoutPlanner visitor(old_buffer);
98 visitor(block);
99 return visitor.Finalize(new_buffer, index_map, inverse, padding_predicate, pad_value);
100 }
101
102 private:
103 struct WriteInfo {
104 // The BufferStore object
105 BufferStore store;
106
107 // The block realize that contains the store, if any.
108 Optional<BlockRealize> innermost_block_realize;
109
110 // The nested loops whose values contribute to the indices used in
111 // the store. Not all loop variables in the loopnest need to
112 // contribute, but the first and last must.
113 std::vector<For> dependent_loopnest;
114
115 // Whether the padding could be represented as a tir::if_then_else
116 // node. This requires that the surrounding loop iterators
117 // iterate over all pre-transformation buffer axes, that there are
118 // no data dependencies between loop iterations, and that
119 bool contains_row_major_traversal{false};
120 };
121
122 explicit TransformLayoutPlanner(Buffer old_buffer) : old_buffer_(old_buffer) {}
123
124 void VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) override {
125 BindLoopVar context(this, GetRef<For>(op));
126 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
127 }
128
129 void VisitStmt_(const LetStmtNode* op) override {
130 BindVariableDefinition context(this, op->var, op->value);
131 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
132 }
133
134 void VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* op) override {
135 BindBlockRealize context(this, GetRef<BlockRealize>(op));
136 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
137 }
138
139 void VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) override {
140 if (!op->buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
141 return;
142 }
143
144 std::optional<std::pair<size_t, size_t>> loop_dependency_range = std::nullopt;
145 for (const auto& index : op->indices) {
146 if (auto index_depth = LoopDependencyRange(index); index_depth.has_value()) {
147 if (loop_dependency_range) {
148 loop_dependency_range = {
149 std::min(loop_dependency_range.value().first, index_depth.value().first),
150 std::max(loop_dependency_range.value().second, index_depth.value().second)};
151 } else {
152 loop_dependency_range = index_depth;
153 }
154 }
155 }
156
157 WriteInfo write_info;
158 write_info.store = GetRef<BufferStore>(op);
159 if (loop_dependency_range) {
160 size_t i = loop_dependency_range.value().first;
161 size_t j = loop_dependency_range.value().second;
162 ICHECK_LT(i, active_loops_.size());
163 ICHECK_LT(j, active_loops_.size());
164
165 write_info.dependent_loopnest = {active_loops_.begin() + i, active_loops_.begin() + j + 1};
166 }
167 write_info.innermost_block_realize = innermost_block_realize_;
168
169 write_info.contains_row_major_traversal = [&]() -> bool {
170 const auto& loopnest = write_info.dependent_loopnest;
171 if (loopnest.empty()) {
172 return false;
173 }
174
175 if (loopnest.size() != old_buffer_->shape.size() || loopnest.size() != op->indices.size()) {
176 return false;
177 }
178
179 for (size_t i = 0; i < loopnest.size(); i++) {
180 const For& loop = loopnest[i];
181 const PrimExpr& buffer_dim = old_buffer_->shape[i];
182 PrimExpr index = Substitute(op->indices[i], active_var_bindings_);
183 bool is_loop_over_axis = index.same_as(loop->loop_var) && is_const_int(loop->min, 0) &&
184 ExprDeepEqual()(loop->extent, buffer_dim) &&
185 loop->kind == ForKind::kSerial;
186 if (!is_loop_over_axis) {
187 return false;
188 }
189 }
190
191 return true;
192 }();
193
194 write_info_.push_back(write_info);
195
196 // Don't need to continue recursing, as the entire goal was to
197 // find the BufferStore.
198 }
199
200 std::optional<std::pair<size_t, size_t>> LoopDependencyRange(const PrimExpr& expr) const {
201 std::optional<std::pair<size_t, size_t>> prev = std::nullopt;
202 for (const auto& var : UndefinedVars(expr)) {
203 auto it = loop_depth_lookup_.find(var.get());
204 if (it != loop_depth_lookup_.end()) {
205 if (prev.has_value()) {
206 prev = {std::min(prev.value().first, it->second.first),
207 std::max(prev.value().second, it->second.second)};
208 } else {
209 prev = it->second;
210 }
211 }
212 }
213
214 return prev;
215 }
216
217 class BufferStoreReplacer : public StmtExprMutator {
218 public:
219 BufferStoreReplacer(const WriteInfo& info, const Buffer& new_buffer, PrimExpr padding_predicate,
220 const IndexMap& inverse, const Optional<IndexMap>& pad_value,
221 Map<Block, Block>* new_block_to_old)
222 : info(info),
223 new_buffer(new_buffer),
224 new_indices(inverse->initial_indices.Map([](const Var& var) -> PrimExpr { return var; })),
225 padding_predicate(padding_predicate),
226 inverse(inverse),
227 pad_value(pad_value),
228 new_block_to_old(*new_block_to_old) {
229 ICHECK_EQ(info.dependent_loopnest.size(), inverse->final_indices.size());
230 for (size_t i = 0; i < info.dependent_loopnest.size(); i++) {
231 Var var = info.dependent_loopnest[i]->loop_var;
232 PrimExpr expr = inverse->final_indices[i];
233 var_remap.Set(var, expr);
234 }
235
236 DefineBlockUpdates();
237 }
238
239 bool is_all_stores_replaced() const { return all_stores_replaced; }
240
241 private:
242 void DefineBlockUpdates() {
243 if (!info.innermost_block_realize) {
244 return;
245 }
246
247 BlockRealize block_realize = info.innermost_block_realize.value();
248 const auto& block = block_realize->block;
249 const Array<PrimExpr>& old_indices = info.store->indices;
250 const auto& old_iter_vars = block->iter_vars;
251
252 this->new_iter_vars = old_iter_vars;
253 this->new_iter_values = block_realize->iter_values;
254
255 if (old_indices.empty()) {
256 return;
257 }
258
259 // Find the block iterators that are used to access the buffer. Must be in the same
260 // order as they appear in the indices.
261 if (block->iter_vars.size() < old_indices.size()) {
262 return;
263 }
264
265 size_t block_index_start = 0;
266 for (; block_index_start < old_iter_vars.size() - old_indices.size(); block_index_start++) {
267 if (old_indices[0].same_as(old_iter_vars[block_index_start]->var)) {
268 break;
269 }
270 }
271 if (block_index_start > old_iter_vars.size() - old_indices.size()) {
272 return;
273 }
274
275 for (size_t i = 0; i < old_indices.size(); i++) {
276 if (!old_indices[i].same_as(old_iter_vars[block_index_start + i]->var) ||
277 old_iter_vars[block_index_start + i]->iter_type != kDataPar) {
278 return;
279 }
280 }
281
282 // If we got to this point, all indices used to access the
283 // buffer are virtual indices defined in the innermost block.
284 // Therefore, generate new virtual indices for iterating over
285 // the post-transform buffer.
286
287 new_indices = inverse->initial_indices.Map([](Var var) -> PrimExpr {
288 std::stringstream ss;
289 ss << "v_" << var->name_hint;
290 return Var(ss.str(), var.dtype());
291 });
292
293 Map<Var, PrimExpr>
294 loop_var_to_virtual_var; // For updating padding_predicate in terms of the new indices
295 Array<PrimExpr> new_iter_values; // For BlockRealize
296 Array<IterVar> new_iter_vars; // For Block
297
298 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_index_start; i++) {
299 new_iter_vars.push_back(old_iter_vars[i]);
300 new_iter_values.push_back(block_realize->iter_values[i]);
301 }
302
303 ICHECK_EQ(new_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
304 for (size_t i = 0; i < new_indices.size(); i++) {
305 Var var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
306 Var virtual_var = Downcast<Var>(new_indices[i]);
307 PrimExpr dim = new_buffer->shape[i];
308 new_iter_values.push_back(var);
309 new_iter_vars.push_back(
310 IterVar(Range::FromMinExtent(make_zero(dim.dtype()), dim), virtual_var, kDataPar));
311 loop_var_to_virtual_var.Set(var, virtual_var);
312 }
313
314 for (size_t i = block_index_start + old_indices.size(); i < old_iter_vars.size(); i++) {
315 new_iter_vars.push_back(old_iter_vars[i]);
316 new_iter_values.push_back(block_realize->iter_values[i]);
317 }
318
319 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->final_indices.size(), old_indices.size());
320 for (size_t i = 0; i < old_indices.size(); i++) {
321 Var var = Downcast<Var>(old_indices[i]);
322 PrimExpr expr = Substitute(inverse->final_indices[i], loop_var_to_virtual_var);
323 var_remap.Set(var, expr);
324 }
325
326 padding_predicate = Substitute(padding_predicate, loop_var_to_virtual_var);
327
328 this->new_iter_vars = new_iter_vars;
329 this->new_iter_values = new_iter_values;
330 }
331
332 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) final {
333 bool can_replace = [&]() -> bool {
334 if (!op->buffer.same_as(info.store->buffer)) {
335 return false;
336 }
337
338 const Array<PrimExpr>& old_indices = info.store->indices;
339
340 ICHECK_EQ(old_indices.size(), op->indices.size());
341 ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
342 for (size_t i = 0; i < old_indices.size(); i++) {
343 if (!expr_equal(old_indices[i], op->indices[i])) {
344 return false;
345 }
346 }
347 return true;
348 }();
349
350 BufferStore store = GetRef<BufferStore>(op);
351 if (can_replace) {
352 PrimExpr pad_value_at_index = pad_value.value()->MapIndices(new_indices)[0];
353 store =
354 BufferStore(new_buffer, if_then_else(padding_predicate, pad_value_at_index, op->value),
355 new_indices);
356 } else {
357 all_stores_replaced = false;
358 }
359 return StmtExprMutator::VisitStmt_(store.get());
360 }
361
362 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* op) final {
363 BlockRealize realize = Downcast<BlockRealize>(StmtExprMutator::VisitStmt_(op));
364
365 if (op == info.innermost_block_realize.get()) {
366 Block block = realize->block;
367 if (!block->iter_vars.same_as(this->new_iter_vars)) {
368 block.CopyOnWrite()->iter_vars = this->new_iter_vars;
369 RecordReplacement(op->block, block);
370 }
371
372 if (!block.same_as(realize->block) ||
373 !realize->iter_values.same_as(this->new_iter_values)) {
374 auto write_ptr = realize.CopyOnWrite();
375 write_ptr->block = block;
376 write_ptr->iter_values = this->new_iter_values;
377 }
378 }
379
380 return std::move(realize);
381 }
382
383 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BlockNode* op) final {
384 Block orig = GetRef<Block>(op);
385 Block mutated = Downcast<Block>(StmtExprMutator::VisitStmt_(op));
386
387 RecordReplacement(orig, mutated);
388 return std::move(mutated);
389 }
390
391 PrimExpr VisitExpr_(const VarNode* op) final {
392 Var var = GetRef<Var>(op);
393 if (auto opt = var_remap.Get(var)) {
394 return opt.value();
395 } else {
396 return std::move(var);
397 }
398 }
399
400 void RecordReplacement(Block before, Block after) {
401 if (before.same_as(after)) {
402 return;
403 }
404
405 ICHECK(!new_block_to_old.count(after));
406
407 while (true) {
408 if (auto opt = new_block_to_old.Get(before)) {
409 before = opt.value();
410 } else {
411 break;
412 }
413 }
414
415 new_block_to_old.Set(after, before);
416 }
417
418 const WriteInfo& info;
419 const Buffer& new_buffer;
420 Array<PrimExpr> new_indices;
421 Array<IterVar> new_iter_vars;
422 Array<PrimExpr> new_iter_values;
423 PrimExpr padding_predicate;
424 const IndexMap& inverse;
425 const Optional<IndexMap>& pad_value;
426 Map<Block, Block>& new_block_to_old;
427 bool all_stores_replaced{true};
428
429 Map<Var, PrimExpr> var_remap;
430 };
431
432 TransformPlan Finalize(Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map, IndexMap inverse,
433 PrimExpr padding_predicate, Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) const {
434 if (auto prologue_plan =
435 FinalizeProloguePlan(new_buffer, index_map, inverse, padding_predicate, pad_value);
436 prologue_plan.has_value()) {
437 return prologue_plan.value();
438 } else if (auto replacement_plan = FinalizeReplacementPlan(new_buffer, index_map, inverse,
439 padding_predicate, pad_value);
440 replacement_plan.has_value()) {
441 return replacement_plan.value();
442 } else if (auto epilogue_plan = FinalizeEpiloguePlan(new_buffer, index_map, inverse,
443 padding_predicate, pad_value);
444 epilogue_plan.has_value()) {
445 return epilogue_plan.value();
446 } else {
447 return NoPaddingRequired();
448 }
449 }
450
451 std::optional<ProloguePlan> FinalizeProloguePlan(Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map,
452 IndexMap inverse, PrimExpr padding_predicate,
453 Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) const {
454 if (write_info_.size() || is_zero(padding_predicate) || !pad_value.defined()) {
455 return std::nullopt;
456 }
457
458 Array<IterVar> iter_vars;
459 Array<PrimExpr> iter_values;
460 Array<PrimExpr> indices;
461 Map<Var, PrimExpr> loop_indices_to_block_indices;
462 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
463 for (size_t i = 0; i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); i++) {
464 const auto& loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
465 const auto& dim = new_buffer->shape[i];
466 Var block_var("v_" + loop_var->name_hint, loop_var->dtype);
467 IterVar iter_var(Range(0, dim), block_var, kDataPar);
468 loop_indices_to_block_indices.Set(loop_var, block_var);
469 indices.push_back(iter_var->var);
470 iter_vars.push_back(iter_var);
471 iter_values.push_back(loop_var);
472 }
473 padding_predicate = Substitute(std::move(padding_predicate), loop_indices_to_block_indices);
474
475 PrimExpr pad_value_at_index = pad_value.value()->MapIndices(indices)[0];
476 PrimExpr expr = (!padding_predicate) || (BufferLoad(new_buffer, indices) == pad_value_at_index);
477 Stmt stmt = Evaluate(Call(DataType::Bool(), builtin::assume(), {expr}));
478
479 std::stringstream block_name;
480 block_name << "buffer_" << new_buffer->name << "_assumptions";
481 auto read_region = BufferRegion::FromPoint(new_buffer, indices);
482 stmt = BlockRealize(iter_values, Bool(true),
483 Block(iter_vars, {read_region}, {}, block_name.str(), stmt));
484
485 for (size_t rev_i = 0; rev_i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); rev_i++) {
486 size_t i = (inverse->initial_indices.size() - 1) - rev_i;
487 Var loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
488 PrimExpr extent = new_buffer->shape[i];
489 stmt = For(loop_var, 0, extent, ForKind::kSerial, stmt);
490 }
491 return ProloguePlan{stmt};
492 }
493
494 std::optional<ReplacementPlan> FinalizeReplacementPlan(Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map,
495 IndexMap inverse,
496 PrimExpr padding_predicate,
497 Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) const {
498 if (write_info_.empty() || is_zero(padding_predicate) || !pad_value.defined()) {
499 return std::nullopt;
500 }
501
502 Map<Block, Block> new_block_to_old;
503 auto generate_if_then_else_block = [&](const WriteInfo& info) -> Optional<Stmt> {
504 if (!info.contains_row_major_traversal || !pad_value.defined() ||
505 is_zero(padding_predicate)) {
506 return NullOpt;
507 }
508
509 BufferStoreReplacer replacer(info, new_buffer, padding_predicate, inverse, pad_value,
510 &new_block_to_old);
511 Stmt stmt = replacer(info.dependent_loopnest.back()->body);
512 if (!replacer.is_all_stores_replaced()) {
513 return NullOpt;
514 }
515
516 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
517 for (size_t rev_i = 0; rev_i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); rev_i++) {
518 size_t i = (inverse->initial_indices.size() - 1) - rev_i;
519 Var loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
520 PrimExpr extent = new_buffer->shape[i];
521 stmt = For(loop_var, 0, extent, ForKind::kSerial, stmt);
522 }
523
524 return stmt;
525 };
526
527 Map<For, Stmt> loop_replacements;
528
529 for (const auto& info : write_info_) {
530 if (info.dependent_loopnest.size()) {
531 if (auto opt_stmt = generate_if_then_else_block(info)) {
532 loop_replacements.Set(info.dependent_loopnest[0], opt_stmt.value());
533 }
534 }
535 }
536
537 if (loop_replacements.size()) {
538 return ReplacementPlan{std::move(loop_replacements), std::move(new_block_to_old)};
539 } else {
540 return std::nullopt;
541 }
542 }
543
544 std::optional<EpiloguePlan> FinalizeEpiloguePlan(Buffer new_buffer, IndexMap index_map,
545 IndexMap inverse, PrimExpr padding_predicate,
546 Optional<IndexMap> pad_value) const {
547 if (write_info_.empty() || is_zero(padding_predicate) || !pad_value.defined()) {
548 return std::nullopt;
549 }
550
551 Array<IterVar> iter_vars;
552 Array<PrimExpr> iter_values;
553 Array<PrimExpr> indices;
554 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
555 for (size_t i = 0; i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); i++) {
556 const auto& loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
557 const auto& dim = new_buffer->shape[i];
558 Var block_var("v_" + loop_var->name_hint, loop_var->dtype);
559 IterVar iter_var(Range(0, dim), block_var, kDataPar);
560 indices.push_back(iter_var->var);
561 iter_vars.push_back(iter_var);
562 iter_values.push_back(loop_var);
563 }
564
565 PrimExpr pad_value_at_index = pad_value.value()->MapIndices(indices)[0];
566 Stmt stmt = BufferStore(new_buffer, pad_value_at_index, indices);
567
568 std::stringstream block_name;
569 block_name << "buffer_" << new_buffer->name << "_padding";
570 auto write_region = BufferRegion::FromPoint(new_buffer, indices);
571 stmt = BlockRealize(iter_values, padding_predicate,
572 Block(iter_vars, {}, {write_region}, block_name.str(), stmt));
573
574 ICHECK_EQ(inverse->initial_indices.size(), new_buffer->shape.size());
575 for (size_t rev_i = 0; rev_i < inverse->initial_indices.size(); rev_i++) {
576 size_t i = (inverse->initial_indices.size() - 1) - rev_i;
577 Var loop_var = inverse->initial_indices[i];
578 PrimExpr extent = new_buffer->shape[i];
579 stmt = For(loop_var, 0, extent, ForKind::kSerial, stmt);
580 }
581
582 const auto& info = write_info_.back();
583 Stmt insert_after = [&]() -> Stmt {
584 if (info.dependent_loopnest.size()) {
585 return info.dependent_loopnest.front();
586 } else if (info.innermost_block_realize) {
587 return info.innermost_block_realize.value();
588 } else {
589 LOG(FATAL) << "Write occured outside of any block/loop";
590 return Stmt();
591 }
592 }();
593 return EpiloguePlan{insert_after, stmt};
594 }
595
596 struct BindLoopVar {
597 BindLoopVar(TransformLayoutPlanner* self, For for_node)
598 : self_(self), var_(for_node->loop_var) {
599 size_t loop_depth = self_->active_loops_.size();
600 self_->loop_depth_lookup_[var_.get()] = {loop_depth, loop_depth};
601 self_->active_loops_.push_back(std::move(for_node));
602 }
603 ~BindLoopVar() {
604 self_->active_loops_.pop_back();
605 self_->loop_depth_lookup_.erase(var_.get());
606 }
607 BindLoopVar(const BindLoopVar&) = delete;
608 BindLoopVar& operator=(const BindLoopVar&) = delete;
609 BindLoopVar(BindLoopVar&&) = delete;
610 BindLoopVar& operator=(BindLoopVar&&) = delete;
611
612 TransformLayoutPlanner* self_{nullptr};
613 Var var_;
614 };
615
616 struct BindVariableDefinition {
617 BindVariableDefinition() {}
618 BindVariableDefinition(TransformLayoutPlanner* self, Var var, PrimExpr value)
619 : self_(self), var_(var) {
620 if (auto loop_depth = self->LoopDependencyRange(value); loop_depth.has_value()) {
621 self_->loop_depth_lookup_[var_.get()] = loop_depth.value();
622 self_->active_var_bindings_[var_.get()] = Substitute(value, self_->active_var_bindings_);
623 }
624 }
625 ~BindVariableDefinition() {
626 if (self_) {
627 self_->loop_depth_lookup_.erase(var_.get());
628 self_->active_var_bindings_.erase(var_.get());
629 }
630 }
631 BindVariableDefinition(const BindVariableDefinition&) = delete;
632 BindVariableDefinition& operator=(const BindVariableDefinition&) = delete;
633 BindVariableDefinition(BindVariableDefinition&& other) : BindVariableDefinition() {
634 swap(other);
635 }
636 BindVariableDefinition& operator=(BindVariableDefinition&& other) {
637 swap(other);
638 return *this;
639 }
640 void swap(BindVariableDefinition& other) {
641 std::swap(self_, other.self_);
642 std::swap(var_, other.var_);
643 }
644
645 TransformLayoutPlanner* self_{nullptr};
646 Var var_;
647 };
648
649 struct BindBlockRealize {
650 BindBlockRealize(TransformLayoutPlanner* self, BlockRealize block_realize) : self_(self) {
651 ICHECK_EQ(block_realize->iter_values.size(), block_realize->block->iter_vars.size());
652 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_realize->iter_values.size(); i++) {
653 bound_vars_.emplace_back(self, block_realize->block->iter_vars[i]->var,
654 block_realize->iter_values[i]);
655 }
656 cache_ = std::move(block_realize);
657 std::swap(self_->innermost_block_realize_, cache_);
658 }
659 ~BindBlockRealize() { std::swap(self_->innermost_block_realize_, cache_); }
660 BindBlockRealize(const BindBlockRealize&) = delete;
661 BindBlockRealize& operator=(const BindBlockRealize&) = delete;
662 BindBlockRealize(BindBlockRealize&&) = delete;
663 BindBlockRealize& operator=(BindBlockRealize&&) = delete;
664
665 TransformLayoutPlanner* self_{nullptr};
666 Optional<BlockRealize> cache_;
667 std::vector<BindVariableDefinition> bound_vars_;
668 };

673 /*! \brief The loop iterators surrounding the current node
674 *
675 * The outermost loop iterator is `active_loops_.front()`, and the
676 * innermost loop iterator is `active_loops_.back()`.

678 * Used to fill the `WriteInfo::dependent_loopnest` field.

682 /*! \brief Lookup for the outer/inner loops
683 *
684 * Used to fill the `WriteInfo::dependent_loopnest` field.

691 * row-major traversal, even if they are rebound in let/block
692 * mappings.
693 */
694 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, PrimExpr> active_var_bindings_;

697 *
698 * Used to fill the `WriteInfo::innermost_block_realize` field..
699 */

706class TransformLayoutRewriter : private arith::IRMutatorWithAnalyzer {
707 public:
708 /*!
709 * \brief Rewrite the access to the buffer after the transformation
710 * \param scope_stmt The parent statement that contains all accesses to the target buffer
711 * \param old_buffer The target buffer before transformation
712 * \param new_buffer The new buffer after transformation
713 * \param index_map The transformation applied to the buffer
714 * \return The new AST rooting at the original parent scope and the map from the old block to the
715 * new block
716 */
717 static std::pair<Stmt, Map<Block, Block>> Rewrite(
718 const Block& scope_stmt, const Buffer& old_buffer, const Buffer& new_buffer,
719 const IndexMap& index_map, const IndexMap& inverse, const PrimExpr& padding_predicate,
720 const Optional<IndexMap>& pad_value) {
721 auto plan = TransformLayoutPlanner::Plan(scope_stmt, old_buffer, new_buffer, index_map, inverse,
722 padding_predicate, pad_value);
723
724 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
725 TransformLayoutRewriter rewriter(old_buffer, new_buffer, index_map, plan, &analyzer);
726 Block result = Downcast<Block>(rewriter(scope_stmt));
727 if (auto plan_ptr = std::get_if<TransformLayoutPlanner::ProloguePlan>(&plan)) {
728 auto write_ptr = result.CopyOnWrite();
729 write_ptr->body = SeqStmt({plan_ptr->prologue, write_ptr->body});
730 }
731
732 Map<Block, Block> block_sref_reuse;
733 for (auto [after, before] : rewriter.new_block_to_old_) {
734 while (auto opt = rewriter.new_block_to_old_.Get(before)) {
735 before = opt.value();
736 }
737 while (auto opt = block_sref_reuse.Get(after)) {
738 after = opt.value();
739 }
740
741 block_sref_reuse.Set(before, after);
742 }
743
744 return {result, block_sref_reuse};
745 }
746
747 private:
748 TransformLayoutRewriter(const Buffer& old_buffer, const Buffer& new_buffer,
749 const IndexMap& index_map,
750 const TransformLayoutPlanner::TransformPlan& plan,
751 arith::Analyzer* analyzer)
752 : IRMutatorWithAnalyzer(analyzer),
753 old_buffer_(old_buffer),
754 new_buffer_(new_buffer),
755 index_map_(index_map),
756 plan_(plan),
757 buffer_data_to_buffer_{{new_buffer->data, new_buffer}} {
758 if (auto plan_ptr = std::get_if<TransformLayoutPlanner::ReplacementPlan>(&plan_)) {
759 new_block_to_old_ = plan_ptr->new_block_to_old;
760 }
761 }
762
763 void RewriteBufferAccess(Buffer* buffer, Array<PrimExpr>* indices) {
764 *buffer = new_buffer_;
765 *indices = index_map_->MapIndices(*indices);
766 (*indices).MutateByApply(
767 [&](const PrimExpr& e) { return SimplifyNonTrivialExpr(e, analyzer_); });
768 }
769
770 using Parent = arith::IRMutatorWithAnalyzer;
771 using Parent::VisitExpr_;
772 using Parent::VisitStmt_;
773
774 Stmt VisitStmt(const Stmt& stmt) final {
775 Stmt output = Parent::VisitStmt(stmt);
776 if (auto plan_ptr = std::get_if<TransformLayoutPlanner::EpiloguePlan>(&plan_)) {
777 if (plan_ptr->insert_after.same_as(stmt)) {
778 return SeqStmt({output, plan_ptr->new_block});
779 }
780 }
781 return output;
782 }
783
784 Stmt VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) final {
785 // Some replacements may include the original string, such as
786 // replacing `loop` with `{loop, post_proc}`. In this case, avoid
787 // infinite recursion.
788
789 For node = GetRef<For>(op);
790 if (auto plan_ptr = std::get_if<TransformLayoutPlanner::ReplacementPlan>(&plan_)) {
791 auto it = plan_ptr->replacements.find(node);
792 if (it != plan_ptr->replacements.end()) {
793 return VisitStmt((*it).second);
794 }
795 }
796 return Parent::VisitStmt_(op);
797 }
798
799 PrimExpr VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
800 BufferLoad buffer_load = Downcast<BufferLoad>(Parent::VisitExpr_(op));
801 if (buffer_load->buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
802 auto* n = buffer_load.CopyOnWrite();
803 RewriteBufferAccess(&n->buffer, &n->indices);
804 }
805 return std::move(buffer_load);
806 }
807
808 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) final {
809 BufferStore buffer_store = Downcast<BufferStore>(Parent::VisitStmt_(op));
810 if (buffer_store->buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
811 auto* n = buffer_store.CopyOnWrite();
812 RewriteBufferAccess(&n->buffer, &n->indices);
813 }
814 return std::move(buffer_store);
815 }
816
817 void RewriteAccessRegion(Array<BufferRegion>* old_access_regions,
818 const Array<BufferRegion>& infered_access_regions) {
819 auto fmutate = [this, &infered_access_regions](const BufferRegion& buffer_region) {
820 if (buffer_region->buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
821 ICHECK(infered_access_regions.size() == 1);
822 return infered_access_regions[0];
823 }
824 return buffer_region;
825 };
826 (*old_access_regions).MutateByApply(fmutate);
827 }
828
829 Stmt VisitStmt_(const BlockNode* op) final {
830 Block orig = [&]() {
831 Block block = GetRef<Block>(op);
832 while (true) {
833 if (auto it = new_block_to_old_.find(block); it != new_block_to_old_.end()) {
834 block = (*it).second;
835 } else {
836 break;
837 }
838 }
839 return block;
840 }();
841
842 Block block = Downcast<Block>(Parent::VisitStmt_(op));
843
844 auto infered_access_regions = GetBlockReadWriteRegion(block, buffer_data_to_buffer_);
845 auto* n = block.CopyOnWrite();
846 RewriteAccessRegion(&n->reads, infered_access_regions[0]);
847 RewriteAccessRegion(&n->writes, infered_access_regions[1]);
848 n->alloc_buffers.MutateByApply([this](const Buffer& buffer) {
849 if (buffer.same_as(old_buffer_)) {
850 return new_buffer_;
851 } else {
852 return buffer;
853 }
854 });
855
856 RecordReplacement(orig, block);
857 return std::move(block);
858 }
859
860 void RecordReplacement(Block before, Block after) {
861 if (before.same_as(after)) {
862 return;
863 }
864
865 ICHECK(!new_block_to_old_.count(after));
866
867 while (true) {
868 if (auto opt = new_block_to_old_.Get(before)) {
869 before = opt.value();
870 } else {
871 break;
872 }
873 }
874
875 new_block_to_old_.Set(after, before);
876 }
877
878 const Buffer& old_buffer_;
879 const Buffer& new_buffer_;
880 const IndexMap& index_map_;
881 const TransformLayoutPlanner::TransformPlan& plan_;
882 Map<Var, Buffer> buffer_data_to_buffer_;
883 Map<Block, Block> new_block_to_old_;
884};

1058void TransformLayout(ScheduleState self, const StmtSRef& block_sref, int buffer_index,
1059 BufferIndexType buffer_index_type, const IndexMap& index_map,
1060 const Optional<IndexMap>& pad_value) {
1061 // Step 1: Input handling and error checking
1062 const BlockNode* block_ptr = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1063 Buffer old_buffer =
1064 GetNthAccessBuffer(self, GetRef<Block>(block_ptr), buffer_index, buffer_index_type);
1065 auto [defining_site_sref, is_alloc] = GetBufferDefiningSite(block_sref, old_buffer);
1066 if (defining_site_sref.defined() && !is_alloc) {
1067 throw BufferIsSubregionError(self->mod, old_buffer);
1068 }
1069 if (pad_value) {
1070 if (pad_value.value()->final_indices.size() != 1) {
1071 throw TransformationPaddingIndexMapError(self->mod, pad_value.value());
1072 }
1073 if (pad_value.value()->final_indices[0]->dtype != old_buffer->dtype) {
1074 throw TransformationPaddingTypeError(self->mod, old_buffer, pad_value.value());
1075 }
1076
1077 TransformationPaddingExpressionError::Check(self->mod, old_buffer, pad_value.value());
1078 }
1079
1080 StmtSRef scope_sref = defining_site_sref.defined()
1081 ? defining_site_sref.value()
1082 : GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref, /*require_stage_pipeline=*/false);
1083 const BlockNode* scope_block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_sref);
1084
1085 auto [inverse, padding_predicate] = [&]() {
1086 Array<Range> region;
1087 for (const auto& dim : old_buffer->shape) {
1088 region.push_back(Range::FromMinExtent(make_zero(dim.dtype()), dim));
1089 }
1090 return index_map.NonSurjectiveInverse(region);
1091 }();
1092
1093 bool has_padding = !is_zero(padding_predicate);
1094 if (has_padding && !pad_value.defined()) {
1095 throw TransformationIntroducesPaddingError(self->mod, old_buffer, index_map, padding_predicate);
1096 }
1097
1098 // Step 2: Infer the shape of the new buffer
1099 Buffer new_buffer = old_buffer;
1100 new_buffer.CopyOnWrite()->shape = index_map->MapShape(old_buffer->shape);
1101
1102 // Step 3: Rewrite BufferLoad/BufferStore access indices, block read/write regions, and block
1103 // alloc_buffers.
1104 auto [new_stmt, block_sref_reuse] =
1105 TransformLayoutRewriter::Rewrite(GetRef<Block>(scope_block), old_buffer, new_buffer,
1106 index_map, inverse, padding_predicate, pad_value);
1107 Block new_scope_block = Downcast<Block>(new_stmt);
1108
1109 // Step 4: Rewrite buffer_map of the PrimFunc if necessary.
1110 if (!defining_site_sref.defined()) {
1111 GlobalVar g_var;
1112 GetRootPrimFunc(self->mod, scope_block, &g_var);
1113 IRModuleNode* new_mod = self->mod.CopyOnWrite();
1114 MapNode* new_map = new_mod->functions.CopyOnWrite();
1115 PrimFunc ref_new_func = Downcast<PrimFunc>(std::move(new_map->at(g_var)));
1116 PrimFuncNode* new_func = ref_new_func.CopyOnWrite();
1117 MapNode* new_buffer_map = new_func->buffer_map.CopyOnWrite();
1118 for (auto it = new_buffer_map->begin(); it != new_buffer_map->end(); ++it) {
1119 if ((*it).second.same_as(old_buffer)) {
1120 (*it).second = new_buffer;
1121 }
1122 }
1123 new_map->at(g_var) = std::move(ref_new_func);
1124 }
1125
1126 // Step 4: Replace the scope block with the new block
1127 self->Replace(scope_sref, new_scope_block, block_sref_reuse);
1128}
1129
1130/*!
1131 * \brief Detect the block iter type assoicated with the expression
1132 *
1133 * This function collects block iters in the expression and check if the block iters have the same
1134 * iter type. The detected iter type is the iter type of the block iters in the expression
1135 * if they have the same iter type, otherwise the detected iter type will be kOpaque.
1136 *
1137 * \param expr The expression
1138 * \param block_iter_type_map The mapping from block iter to iter type
1139 * \return The detected block iter type
1140 */
1141IterVarType DetectNewBlockIterType(
1142 const PrimExpr& expr,
1143 const std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, IterVarType>& block_iter_type_map) {
1144 IterVarType result{kOpaque};
1145 bool found = false;
1146 PostOrderVisit(expr, [&](const ObjectRef& obj) {
1147 if (const VarNode* var = obj.as<VarNode>()) {
1148 auto it = block_iter_type_map.find(var);
1149 if (it != block_iter_type_map.end()) {
1150 if (!found) {
1151 found = true;
1152 result = it->second;
1153 } else if (result != it->second) {
1154 result = kOpaque;
1155 return false;
1156 }
1157 }
1158 }
1159 return true;
1160 });
1161 return result;
1162}

1247void TransformBlockLayout(ScheduleState self, const StmtSRef& block_sref,
1248 const IndexMap& index_map) {
1249 const BlockNode* block_ptr = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1250 const Block& block = GetRef<Block>(block_ptr);
1251 arith::Analyzer analyzer;
1252
1253 // Step 1: Collect outer loops and loop vars
1254 Array<StmtSRef> loops = GetLoops(block_sref); // outer loops of the block
1255 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*> loop_vars; // loop vars of the outer loops
1256 for (const StmtSRef& loop_sref : loops) {
1257 CheckLoopStartsWithZero(self, loop_sref, &analyzer);
1258 loop_vars.emplace(loop_sref->StmtAs<ForNode>()->loop_var.get());
1259 }
1260
1261 // Step 2: Check the all outer loops have a single child and the block bindings are trivial (all
1262 // binding values are loop vars)
1263 StmtSRef scope_sref{nullptr}; // the scope statement for replacement
1264 if (!loops.empty()) {
1265 scope_sref = loops.front();
1266 CheckGetSingleChildBlockRealizeOnSRefTree(self, loops.front());
1267 } else {
1268 scope_sref = block_sref;
1269 }
1270
1271 BlockRealize block_realize = GetBlockRealize(self, block_sref);
1272 CheckBlockHasTrivialBinding(self, block_sref);
1273
1274 // Step 3: Collect information of block iter vars
1275 Array<PrimExpr> block_vars; // iter_var->var of each block iter
1276 Map<Var, Range> block_iter_dom; // domain of block iter
1277 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, IterVarType> block_iter_type; // iter type of block iter
1278
1279 Array<PrimExpr>
1280 block_iter_range_array; // array of block iter extents in the same order as block iters
1281 for (const auto& iter_var : block->iter_vars) {
1282 block_vars.push_back(iter_var->var);
1283 block_iter_dom.Set(iter_var->var, iter_var->dom);
1284 block_iter_type[iter_var->var.get()] = iter_var->iter_type;
1285 ICHECK(is_zero(iter_var->dom->min));
1286 block_iter_range_array.push_back(iter_var->dom->extent);
1287 }
1288
1289 // Step 4: Apply the IndexMap to block iters.
1290 IndexMapNotApplicableToBlockIterError::Check(self->mod, block, index_map);
1291 Array<PrimExpr> transformed_block_iters = index_map->MapIndices(block_vars);
1292 Array<PrimExpr> new_block_iter_range = index_map->MapShape(block_iter_range_array);
1293
1294 // Step 5: Create the new block after transformation.
1295
1296 // Step 5.1: Create new block iters. After applying the IndexMap f to block iters ax_0, ..., ax_n,
1297 // create block iter each expression in f(ax_0, ..., ax_n).
1298 Array<IterVar> new_block_iters; // new block iters
1299 Array<PrimExpr> new_block_vars; // iter_var->var of new block iters
1300 for (size_t i = 0; i < transformed_block_iters.size(); ++i) {
1301 Var new_block_var{"v" + std::to_string(i), transformed_block_iters[i]->dtype};
1302 new_block_vars.push_back(new_block_var);
1303 IterVarType iter_type = DetectNewBlockIterType(transformed_block_iters[i], block_iter_type);
1304 if (iter_type == kOpaque) {
1305 throw OpaqueNewIterTypeError(self->mod, GetRef<Block>(block_ptr), transformed_block_iters[i]);
1306 }
1307 auto dtype = new_block_var.dtype();
1308 new_block_iters.push_back(IterVar(
1309 /*dom=*/Range::FromMinExtent(make_zero(dtype), new_block_iter_range[i]),
1310 /*var=*/std::move(new_block_var), /*iter_type=*/iter_type));
1311 }
1312
1313 // Step 5.2: Update the block body. Use the inverse map f^{-1} to replace the original block iters
1314 // in the body.
1315 Map<Var, PrimExpr> inverse_subst_map;
1316 // Construct the inverse map
1317 {
1318 Array<Range> initial_ranges;
1319 for (const PrimExpr& extent : block_iter_range_array) {
1320 initial_ranges.push_back(Range::FromMinExtent(make_const(extent.dtype(), 0), extent));
1321 }
1322 IndexMap inverse_index_map{nullptr};
1323 try {
1324 inverse_index_map = index_map.Inverse(initial_ranges);
1325 } catch (...) {
1326 throw NotBijectiveAffineIndexMapError(self->mod, index_map);
1327 }
1328
1329 Array<PrimExpr> inversed_new_block_vars = inverse_index_map->MapIndices(
1330 new_block_vars); // old block vars written in terms of new block vars
1331
1332 for (int i = 0, n = block_vars.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1333 inverse_subst_map.Set(Downcast<Var>(block_vars[i]), inversed_new_block_vars[i]);
1334 }
1335 }
1336 Block new_block = Downcast<Block>(Substitute(GetRef<Block>(block_ptr), inverse_subst_map));
1337 new_block.CopyOnWrite()->iter_vars = new_block_iters;
1338 new_block = Downcast<Block>(BlockBufferAccessSimplifier::Simplify(new_block, &analyzer));
1339
1340 // Step 5.3: Create outer loops for each new block iter.
1341
1342 // Make new loop vars
1343 Array<PrimExpr> new_loop_vars;
1344 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(new_block_iters.size()); ++i) {
1345 new_loop_vars.push_back(Var("ax" + std::to_string(i), new_block_iters[i]->var.dtype()));
1346 }
1347
1348 // Make new block realize
1349 BlockRealizeNode* new_block_realize = block_realize.CopyOnWrite();
1350 new_block_realize->iter_values = new_loop_vars;
1351 new_block_realize->block = new_block;
1352
1353 // Generate outer loops
1354 Stmt body = GetRef<Stmt>(new_block_realize);
1355 for (int i = static_cast<int>(new_loop_vars.size()) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
1356 body = For(Downcast<Var>(new_loop_vars[i]), 0, new_block_iter_range[i], ForKind::kSerial,
1357 std::move(body));
1358 }
1359
1360 // Step 6: Do the actual replacement
1361 self->Replace(scope_sref, body, {{block, new_block}});
1362}
1363
1364class BufferAxisSeparatorMutator : private ReplaceBufferMutator {
1365 public:
1366 static Block Mutate(const Block& scope_block, const Buffer& old_buffer, Buffer new_buffer,
1367 Map<Block, Block>* block_sref_reuse) {
1368 BufferAxisSeparatorMutator mutator(old_buffer, std::move(new_buffer), block_sref_reuse);
1369 return Downcast<Block>(mutator.VisitStmt(scope_block));
1370 }
1371
1372 private:
1373 BufferAxisSeparatorMutator(const Buffer& old_buffer, Buffer new_buffer,
1374 Map<Block, Block>* block_sref_reuse)
1375 : ReplaceBufferMutator(old_buffer, new_buffer, block_sref_reuse) {}
1376
1377 MatchBufferRegion VisitMatchBufferRegion(const MatchBufferRegion& match_buffer) final {
1378 auto it = buffer_var_map_.find(match_buffer->source->buffer->data.get());
1379 if (it != buffer_var_map_.end()) {
1380 const Buffer& new_source_buffer = it->second;
1381 Buffer new_target_buffer = match_buffer->buffer;
1382 new_target_buffer.CopyOnWrite()->axis_separators = new_source_buffer->axis_separators;
1383 if (new_target_buffer->shape.size() != new_source_buffer->shape.size()) {
1384 LOG(WARNING)
1385 << "Target buffer in match_buffer doesn't have the same dimensionality as its source "
1386 "buffer. `axis_separators` for the target buffer might be incorrect.";
1387 }
1388 buffer_var_map_[new_target_buffer->data.get()] = new_target_buffer;
1389 return MatchBufferRegion(new_target_buffer,
1390 BufferRegion(new_source_buffer, match_buffer->source->region));
1391 }
1392 return match_buffer;
1393 }
1394};
1395
1396void SetAxisSeparator(ScheduleState self, const StmtSRef& block_sref, int buffer_index,
1397 BufferIndexType buffer_index_type, const Array<IntImm>& axis_separators) {
1398 const BlockNode* block_ptr = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(block_sref);
1399 Buffer old_buffer =
1400 GetNthAccessBuffer(self, GetRef<Block>(block_ptr), buffer_index, buffer_index_type);
1401 auto [defining_site_sref, is_alloc] = GetBufferDefiningSite(block_sref, old_buffer);
1402 if (defining_site_sref.defined() && !is_alloc) {
1403 throw BufferIsSubregionError(self->mod, old_buffer);
1404 }
1405
1406 StmtSRef scope_sref = defining_site_sref.defined()
1407 ? defining_site_sref.value()
1408 : GetScopeRoot(self, block_sref, /*require_stage_pipeline=*/false);
1409 const BlockNode* scope_block = TVM_SREF_TO_BLOCK(scope_sref);
1410
1411 // Step 1: Check and update axis_separators of the buffer.
1412 Buffer new_buffer = old_buffer;
1413 new_buffer.CopyOnWrite()->axis_separators = axis_separators;
1414
1415 Map<Block, Block> block_sref_reuse;
1416
1417 // Step 2: Rewrite alloc_buffer of the block or buffer_map of the PrimFunc.
1418 Block new_scope_block = BufferAxisSeparatorMutator::Mutate(GetRef<Block>(scope_block), old_buffer,
1419 new_buffer, &block_sref_reuse);
1420 if (!defining_site_sref.defined()) {
1421 // mutate buffer_map of the PrimFunc
1422 GlobalVar g_var;
1423 GetRootPrimFunc(self->mod, scope_block, &g_var);
1424 IRModuleNode* new_mod = self->mod.CopyOnWrite();
1425 MapNode* new_map = new_mod->functions.CopyOnWrite();
1426 PrimFunc ref_new_func = Downcast<PrimFunc>(std::move(new_map->at(g_var)));
1427 PrimFuncNode* new_func = ref_new_func.CopyOnWrite();
1428 MapNode* new_buffer_map = new_func->buffer_map.CopyOnWrite();
1429 for (auto it = new_buffer_map->begin(); it != new_buffer_map->end(); ++it) {
1430 if ((*it).second.same_as(old_buffer)) {
1431 (*it).second = new_buffer;
1432 }
1433 }
1434 new_map->at(g_var) = std::move(ref_new_func);
1435 }
1436
1437 // Step 4: Replace the scope block with the new block
1438 self->Replace(scope_sref, new_scope_block, block_sref_reuse);
1439}
